hip between China and France and the spirit of the Olympics and conveys a message of peace.\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 790, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 655, \"end\": 660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.773924922694735e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 711, \"end\": 716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9956412400194028, \"rank\": 0.004343333212626844, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 721, \"end\": 727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995124659759582, \"rank\": 0.00037776409775061527, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Named \\\"Tong Zhou Gong Du,\\\" meaning \\\"cross a river in the same boat,\\\" the sculpture was created by renowned Chinese sculptor Huang Jian, the International Olympic Committee's art ambassador, and was donated by CMG to the French Olympic Committee.\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 1037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 799, \"end\": 803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tong_Jian\", \"score\": 0.8407321394451288, \"rank\": 0.18943947749857853, \"text\": \"Tong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tong_Jian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tong_Jian\"}, {\"begin\": 804, \"end\": 813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke_of_Zhou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zhou Gong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke_of_Zhou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke_of_Zhou\"}, {\"begin\": 899, \"end\": 906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.9971625382930102, \"rank\": 0.002248791943836495, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 916, \"end\": 926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huang_Jian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Huang Jian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huang_Jian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huang_Jian\"}, {\"begin\": 932, \"end\": 963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1001, \"end\": 1004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Media_Group\", \"score\": 0.9989996507883976, \"rank\": 0.0010013507747988993, \"text\": \"CMG\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Media_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Media_Group\"}, {\"begin\": 1012, \"end\": 1036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_National_Olympic_and_Sports_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_National_Olympic_and_Sports_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_National_Olympic_and_Sports_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics-themed sculpture named \\\"Tong Zhou Gong Du,\\\" meaning \\\"cross a river in the same boat,\\\" by Chinese artist Huang Jian is inaugurated at Ch\\u00c3\\u00a2teau de Catala in Paris, France, September 6, 2024.\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1076, \"end\": 1080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tong_Jian\", \"score\": 0.8407321394451288, \"rank\": 0.18943947749857853, \"text\": \"Tong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tong_Jian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tong_Jian\"}, {\"begin\": 1081, \"end\": 1090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke_of_Zhou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zhou Gong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke_of_Zhou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke_of_Zhou\"}, {\"begin\": 1141, \"end\": 1148, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.9971625382930102, \"rank\": 0.002248791943836495, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1156, \"end\": 1166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huang_Jian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Huang Jian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huang_Jian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huang_Jian\"}, {\"begin\": 1207, \"end\": 1212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.773924922694735e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1214, \"end\": 1220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995124659759582, \"rank\": 0.00037776409775061527, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CMG  Shen Haixiong, vice minister of the Publicity Department of the Communist Party of China Central Committee and president of CMG, sent a congratulatory letter to the event.\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1247, \"end\": 1260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shen_Haixiong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shen Haixiong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shen_Haixiong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shen_Haixiong\"}, {\"begin\": 1371, \"end\": 1374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Media_Group\", \"score\": 0.9989996507883976, \"rank\": 0.0010013507747988993, \"text\": \"CMG\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Media_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Media_Group\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the letter, Shen Haixiong said as a gift of friendship, the sculpture commemorates the 60th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between China and France and sends blessings to the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 1420, \"to\": 1639, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1435, \"end\": 1448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shen_Haixiong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shen Haixiong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shen_Haixiong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shen_Haixiong\"}, {\"begin\": 1580, \"end\": 1585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9956412400194028, \"rank\": 0.004343333212626844, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1590, \"end\": 1596, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995124659759582, \"rank\": 0.00037776409775061527, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We expect people from all walks of life in China and France will continue to take the Olympics as a bond, jointly promote exchanges and dialogues among different civilizations, promote mutual understanding and respect among peoples, jointly write a more glorious chapter in the Olympic Movement, and contribute new and greater strength to building a community with a shared future for mankind,\\\" Shen wrote in the letter.\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 2062, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1685, \"end\": 1690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9956412400194028, \"rank\": 0.004343333212626844, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1695, \"end\": 1701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995124659759582, \"rank\": 0.00037776409775061527, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1920, \"end\": 1936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9276060531643427, \"rank\": 0.0780438490981738, \"text\": \"Olympic Movement\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sculpture was created by Chinese artist Huang Jian.\", \"from\": 2064, \"to\": 2119, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2093, \"end\": 2100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.9971625382930102, \"rank\": 0.002248791943836495, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2108, \"end\": 2118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huang_Jian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Huang Jian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huang_Jian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Huang_Jian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CMG  Lu Shaye, China's ambassador to France, St\\u00c3\\u00a9phane Hatot, cultural counselor of the French National Olympic Committee, and Brigitte Marsigny, Mayor of French city Noisy-le-Grand, attended the event and delivered speeches.\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2126, \"end\": 2134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lu_Shaye\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lu Shaye\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lu_Shaye\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lu_Shaye\"}, {\"begin\": 2136, \"end\": 2141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9956412400194028, \"rank\": 0.004343333212626844, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2158, \"end\": 2164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995124659759582, \"rank\": 0.00037776409775061527, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2209, \"end\": 2215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9947660421567016, \"rank\": 0.00489205161490504, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2216, \"end\": 2242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.999999710519247, \"rank\": 1.4673326147649803e-07, \"text\": \"National Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2276, \"end\": 2282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9947660421567016, \"rank\": 0.00489205161490504, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ambassador Lu Shaye said this sculpture conveys the concepts of unity, peace and friendship through the combination of sports and culture, expressing the pursuit of the Olympic spirit and the expectations for world peace by both China and France.\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2359, \"end\": 2367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lu_Shaye\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lu Shaye\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lu_Shaye\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lu_Shaye\"}, {\"begin\": 2577, \"end\": 2582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9956412400194028, \"rank\": 0.004343333212626844, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2587, \"end\": 2593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995124659759582, \"rank\": 0.00037776409775061527, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We expect this sculpture to become a new landmark for the city Noisy-le-Grand, demonstrating the vitality of the friendly relations between China and France,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2595, \"to\": 2763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2659, \"end\": 2673, \"title\": \"http:/