said.\", \"from\": 2956, \"to\": 3131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3050, \"end\": 3056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9995124659759582, \"rank\": 0.00037776409775061527, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3061, \"end\": 3066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9956412400194028, \"rank\": 0.004343333212626844, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brigitte Marsigny, Mayor of French city Noisy-le-Grand, said that art has the power to transcend national boundaries to touch people's hearts.\", \"from\": 3133, \"to\": 3275, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3161, \"end\": 3167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9947660421567016, \"rank\": 0.00489205161490504, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics-themed sculpture \\\"Tong Zhou Gong Du\\\" features a boat with symbols\\u00a0of both Chinese and French cultures: the Chinese dragon and the Gallic rooster.\", \"from\": 3277, \"to\": 3435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3308, \"end\": 3312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tong_Jian\", \"score\": 0.8407321394451288, \"rank\": 0.18943947749857853, \"text\": \"Tong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tong_Jian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tong_Jian\"}, {\"begin\": 3313, \"end\": 3322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke_of_Zhou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zhou Gong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.